BUG: AsyncApiDocumentGenerator accumulates state in _channels, _operations, _messages dictionaries across calls. It is registered as a singleton via the DI factory in AsyncApiBrighterBuilderExtensions.cs:63. On second call to GenerateAsync(), existing entries are still in the dictionaries, causing GetUniqueOperationId to produce _2 suffixed IDs and corrupt the document.

FIX: Add three .Clear() calls at the top of GenerateAsync():
  _channels.Clear();
  _operations.Clear();
  _messages.Clear();

