P1 ISSUE: AsyncApiHostExtensions.cs:68-71 contains:
  public static AsyncApiDocument GenerateAsyncApiDocument(this IHost host, string outputPath)
  {
      return host.GenerateAsyncApiDocumentAsync(outputPath).GetAwaiter().GetResult();
  }

.GetAwaiter().GetResult() is a known deadlock risk when called from contexts with a SynchronizationContext (ASP.NET, WPF, etc.). Since this is a public API on IHost, it's plausible someone calls it from middleware or a controller.

The async method GenerateAsyncApiDocumentAsync is the correct API. The sync wrapper adds risk with no benefit — remove it entirely rather than marking it [Obsolete], since this is pre-release code.

