P1 ISSUE: Multiple methods in AsyncApiDocumentGenerator use the ContainsKey-then-indexer anti-pattern which does two hash lookups instead of one:

1. EnsureChannel (line ~238): if (!_channels.ContainsKey(channelId)) _channels[channelId] = ...
2. EnsureMessageAsync (line ~250): if (!_messages.ContainsKey(messageName)) _messages[messageName] = ...
3. EnsurePlaceholderMessage (line ~262): same pattern
4. AddChannelMessageRef (line ~278): channel.Messages.ContainsKey then channel.Messages[messageName] = ...
5. GetUniqueOperationId (line ~287): _operations.ContainsKey check

NOTE: If US-018 moves these to local variables, apply TryAdd to the local variable versions.
NOTE: For EnsureMessageAsync, TryAdd won't work directly because the value requires an async call. Use CollectionsMarshal.GetValueRefOrAddDefault (NET8+) or check-then-add with TryGetValue pattern:
  if (!_messages.TryGetValue(messageName, out _))
  {
      _messages[messageName] = new AsyncApiMessage { ... };
  }

